---
import FixedSidebarLayout from '../layouts/FixedSidebarLayout.astro';
import YellowBgFooter from '../layouts/YellowBgFooter.astro';
import "../styles/global.css";
---
<FixedSidebarLayout title="Work">
   <main class="work-page">
    <section class="work-grid">
      <div class="work-pair item1">
      <a href="/Illustrations" class="work-item ">
      <div class="work-item">
        <img src="/images/works/illustration1.webp" alt="Illustration" />
        <div class="overlay">Illustration</div>
      </div>
      </a>
      <div class="work-text">
            <p>Our brains process visuals 60,000 times faster than text which is why I use illustration to say what words can’t.Every line and colour carries <span class="highlight"> emotion</span>, creating a <span class="highlight">connection</span> long before a sentence can be read. To me, drawing is not decoration, it’s <span class="highlight">storytelling </span>without translation.</p>
          </div>
          </div>
<div class="work-pair  item2">
  <a href="/kids" class="work-item ">
      <div class="work-item">
        <img src="/images/works/kids.webp" alt="Kids" />
        <div class="overlay">KIDS</div>
      </div>
      </a>
      <div class="work-text">
            <p>Children’s books with illustrations are proven to boost <span class="highlight">imagination</span>, vocabulary, and emotional intelligence. Designing for young minds means thinking in bright shapes, playful proportions, and limitless possibilities. Every choice is a chance to make their world feel bigger, kinder, and more <span class="highlight">magical</span>.</p>
          </div>
          </div>
        <div class="work-pair reverse item3">
         <a href="/works/mycity" class="work-item  ">

      <div class="work-item">
        <img src="/images/works/mycity.webp" alt="My City" />
        <div class="overlay">My City</div>
      </div>
      </a>
      <div class="work-text">
            <p>Every city has a visual rhythm — from the colours of its walls to the <span class="highlight">patterns</span> in its markets.Vadodara speaks in the quiet details of its streets, the hum of its <span class="highlight">people</span>, and the textures of its <span class="highlight">history</span>.I capture those moments so the place can be felt, not just seen.</p>
          </div>
          </div>
      <div class="work-pair item4">
      <a href="/works/graphics" class="work-item  ">
       <div class="work-item">
        <img src="/images/works/graphics.webp" alt="Graphics" />
        <div class="overlay">Graphics</div>
      </div>
      </a>
      <div class="work-text">
            <p>Good graphic design increases brand recognition by up to 80% — but numbers aren’t the whole story. Design is about shaping an <span class="highlight">identity </span> that speaks even before words are read.It’s where clarity meets creativity, and where form carries <span class="highlight">meaning</span>.</p>
          </div>
          </div>
          <div class="work-pair item5">
          <a href="/works/userexperience" class="work-item ">
          <div class="work-item">
          <img src="/images/works/userexperience.webp" alt="User Experience" />
         <div class="overlay">User Experience</div>
         </div>
          </a>
          <div class="work-text">
            <p>A one-second delay in load time can reduce user satisfaction by 16% — but great UX is about more than speed. It’s about designing<span class="highlight"> invisible pathways </span> that feel natural to follow. When it works well, people don’t <span class="highlight"> notice the design </span>— they just feel understood .</p>
          </div>
          </div>
      <div class="work-pair reverse item6">
      <a href="/works/architecture" class="work-item ">
      <div class="work-item">
        <img src="/images/works/architecture.webp" alt="Architecture" />
        <div class="overlay">Architecture</div>
      </div>
      </a>
      <div class="work-text">
            <p>Architecture shapes how we feel without us realising. From the openness of a courtyard to the quiet of a reading nook, design silently directs <span class="highlight"> experience</span>. Spaces are stories in three dimensions — and I believe every detail should be <span class="highlight">intentional</span>.</p>
          </div>
          </div>

      </section>
      <YellowBgFooter />
      </FixedSidebarLayout>
</FixedSidebarLayout>
<style>
  .work-grid {
    padding-left: 20px;
      padding-top: 3rem;
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(5, auto);
      grid-template-rows: repeat(6, auto);
      gap: 4rem 2rem;
      margin: 0 auto;
      justify-items: center;
      position: relative;
       max-width: 1500px;
    }
    .work-item {
       flex: 0 0 300px;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: row;
      align-items: center;
      font-family: 'Lilita One', cursive;
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
      border-radius: 0.5rem; /*box-shadow: 0 5px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);*/
      transition: transform 0.3s;
    }
    .work-pair {
      display: flex;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: 1.5rem;
      box-sizing: border-box;
       width: 100%;
     }

    .work-item img {
      display: flex;
      align-items: flex-start;
      width: 100%;
      height: auto;
      object-fit: contain;
      display: block;
      transition: transform 0.3s ease;
    }
    .work-text {
      display: flex;
      align-items: flex-start;
      flex: 1;
      font-family: 'Source Sans 3', sans-serif;
      font-size: 18px;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #fefcb8;
       max-width: 500px;
      }

      .work-text p {
  margin: 0;
}

    .item1{
       grid-area: 1 / 1 / 2 / 2;
       width: 700px;
  height: auto;
    }
    .item2{
      grid-area: 2 / 2 / 3 / 3 ;
      transform: translateY(-100px);
       width: 600px;
  height: auto;
    }
    .item3{
      grid-area: 3 / 1 / 4 / 2;
       width: 650px;
        height: auto;
        transform: translateY(-100px);
    }
    .item4{
      grid-area: 4 / 2 / 5 / 3;
      width: 550px;
       height: auto;

    }
    .item5{
      grid-area: 5 / 1 / 6 / 2;
       width: 700px;
       height: auto;
    }
    .item6{
    grid-area:  6 / 2 / 7 / 3;
     width: 650px;
     height: auto;
    }
    .work-item:hover img {
      transform: scale(1.05);
    }

    .overlay {. /*font-family: 'Source Sans 3', sans-serif;*/
  font-family: 'Lilita One', cursive;
  position: absolute;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  height: 100%;
  width: 100%;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  background-color: rgba(248, 210, 39, 0.554);
  color: white;
  font-weight: bold;
  font-size: 1.8rem;
  text-align: center;
  opacity: 0;
  transition: opacity 0.3s ease;
}
.highlight {
  font-size: 20px;
  font-weight: bold;
  color: #fbd21a;
  background-color: white;
  padding: 0.1em 0.3em;
  border-radius: 5px;
  display: inline-block;
  box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
}
.work-item:hover .overlay {
  opacity: 1;
}

.work-item:hover img {
  opacity: 0.4;
}
.work-text {
  transition: all 0.5s ease;
}

.work-text:hover {
  transform: translateY(-5px);
  opacity: 0.8;
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .work-pair,
  .work-pair.reverse {
    flex-direction: column;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .work-text {
    max-width: 100%;
  }
}
.work-pair.reverse {
  flex-direction: row-reverse;
}
</style>
